PPN part 16! Leaving the Flower town a little girl asks for help saving her dad from Galactic, I go to the windmills to help but see grass so obvs I jump in to see what Pokémon I get. Shellos appears and breaks many balls. She appears a mighty warrior princess. I name her Xena.

PPN Part 15! I arrive in the Flower Town. This is amazing cause a little girl teaches Kota the move pluck, and he is finally useful and can contribute. Also the first Berry bushes. Things got a little less scary now that I have an Oran Berry. #falseconfidence

PPN part 14! A double battle goes awry. The Pachirisu gang up on Gannondoof and crit him. And I just realize Gannon is a she. I still think the name fits, she’s a tank and pull through. Also, Kazza hits level 15 and I realize I don’t know what level they obey me until....

Pokémon Pearl Nuzlocke Part 13! (Will now be called PPN to shorten character count) in the cave I find a psyduck. In a town someone said Yellow was a bad name for a psyduck. So I name him Yellowcard. I now imagine him in the Ocean Avenue video. #ificouldfindyounow

Pokémon Pearl Nuzlocke Part 12! The team is shaken and we heal. Now that I can use rock smash, I move out and fight some grunts. Starlord eats their Wurmple. Before I go north, I go west and find a good rod. I try fishing for 10 minutes but no bites. Will try again later.

Pokémon Pearl Nuzlocke Part 11! I decide to trust in Swisschar and go for a Mach Punch. If he goes down, maybe Gannondoof can finish him off and keep my losses to a minimum. I drop my DS lite as Swiss pulls of a critical hit, one-shotting Cranidos. Everyone makes it out alive.

Pokémon Pearl Nuzlocke Part 10! I debate switching in my weaker friends to chip away at Cranidos’ life. But I’m uncertain if Swisschar would survive being swapped back in because of stealth rock. One of my rules was no man made healing items in battles.

Pokémon Pearl Nuzlocke Part 9! I stick it out cause stealth rocks are up. Swiss gains a level after the 2nd Pokémon in gym leader fight, bringing his HP out of red. But now we have Cranidos to take out. Worried about losing my starter, I consider making a hard choice.

Pokémon Pearl Nuzlocke Part 8! I prep for gym #1. I still start with Kota in slot one so his happiness will go up. Swisschar takes a hard crit.  Forgot to give him the berry Kazza has. Gannondoof is my only other choice for fighting moves with rock smash, but he lvl 9...

Pokémon Pearl Nuzlocke Part 7! In the Oreburgh mine, Onyxia the Onyx joins. I quickly realize how frustrating it is to level Kota and Kazza by swapping to Swisschar. Luckily he evolves and learns Mach punch which makes life much, much easier. Forgot he becomes a fighting type!

Pokémon Pearl Nuzlocke Part 6! A Machop named Suey, and a Geodude named Golite have come along now. Too afraid to crit catchable Mons so I just throw the balls and hope. Oreburgh offers me a trade of Machop for Abra. After a half hour of internal debate, Kazaa the Abra joins.

Pokémon Pearl Nuzlocke Part 5!  An error has been made. Was watching anime while grinding and failed to notice a Kricketot using Bide. Volvo was taken out by his own strength. RIP little guy. I’ll have to pay more attention during this it seems.

Pokémon Pearl Nuzlocke Part 4! A Zubat has joined me, he was named Kota. However he severely struggles to kill things so I was swapping in Volvo to level them both up. Slaying all of the Kirckets and Birds and Beavers around!

Pokémon Pearl Nuzlocke Part 3! Restarted, game now saves. Just learning I had to save frequently in case this issue persists. Caught a Starly named Starlord, Bidoof named Gannondoof, and a Shinx named Volvo. We are unstoppable.

Pokémon Pearl Nuzlocke part 2!
This was of course done in honor of the remakes being announced. Started my journey and caught my first three friends. Only when I went to save my game, it actually failed to save, telling me to take out the game. So unfortunately restart time!
